body:
Hi @mjmasn, thanks for the issue!

I can reproduce in the [demo](https://eslint.org/demo/#eyJ0ZXh0IjoiLyogZXNsaW50IHByZWZlci1jb25zdDogZXJyb3IgKi9cclxuXHJcbmNvbnN0IGIgPSBbMSwgMl07XHJcbmxldCBhO1xyXG5cclxuIiwib3B0aW9ucyI6eyJwYXJzZXJPcHRpb25zIjp7ImVjbWFWZXJzaW9uIjo2LCJzb3VyY2VUeXBlIjoic2NyaXB0IiwiZWNtYUZlYXR1cmVzIjp7fX0sInJ1bGVzIjp7fSwiZW52Ijp7fX19). I'll mark this as a bug.

:+1: BTW changing https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/196c1021c070e52259f2ceccc4f141bdb7456c60/lib/rules/prefer-const.js#L173 to
```js
.map(element => element ? element.name : null)
```
fixes the crash but I'm not sure if there are any wider implications...
Thanks @mjmasn, that makes sense. Would you like to create a PR (maybe with a new test that would trigger the crash)?
Just out of curiosity, anyone know if this can be recreated in the 4.x release line?

issue.title: Fix: Prefer-const rule crashing on array destructuring (fixes #10520)

body: @platinumazure I don't think so, the code was introduced in https://github.com/eslint/eslint/commit/240c1a4df321de56c12acbcfad21734944d7e116 (first released in [5.0.0-alpha.4](https://github.com/eslint/eslint/releases/tag/v5.0.0-alpha.4))
should we release a patch `5.0.2`, since seems it was introduced in `5.0.0-alpha.4`? cc @eslint/eslint-team
